  "prompt": "What is the monarchy in the United Kingdom?",
  "response": "The monarchy in the United Kingdom is a constitutional monarchy, where the monarch (currently King Charles III) serves as the head of state, but has limited political power. Key points include:\n\n1. Role:\n- Ceremonial figurehead of the nation\n- Symbol of national unity\n- Performs constitutional and representative duties\n\n2. Succession:\n- Hereditary monarchy within the Royal Family\n- Currently, the line of succession follows King Charles III, then Prince William, and then Prince George\n\n3. Powers:\n- Formally appoints the Prime Minister\n- Signs legislation into law\n- Serves as Head of the Church of England\n- Represents the UK in diplomatic functions\n\n4. Current Monarch:\n- King Charles III (succeeded Queen Elizabeth II in September 2022)\n- Part of the Windsor royal family\n\n5. Constitutional Limitations:\n- Monarch's political power is largely ceremonial\n- Must act on advice of elected government\n- Does not make significant political decisions independently\n\n6. Financial Support:\n- Receives public funding through the Sovereign Grant\n- Owns significant property and assets\n\nThe British monarchy is a traditional institution with historical significance, deeply embedded in the country's cultural and political landscape.",
